  "response": "Finding a video that isolates *every single* instrument in \"Strong and Strike\" from Toshiro Masuda in perfect clarity and synchronization might be difficult, as that's not typically how soundtracks are presented outside of studio sessions. However, here's a breakdown of what you can find and how to approach it:\n\n**What you *CAN* find:**\n\n*   **The Original Song:** The most obvious. You can easily find the official release of \"Strong and Strike\" on YouTube, Spotify, Apple Music, and other streaming platforms.\n\n*   **Synthesia/Piano Tutorials:** These often focus on the main melodic lines and chords, giving you insight into the piano/keyboard part. While not *every* instrument, they can help you understand the harmonic structure.\n\n*   **Sheet Music:** While it might not be a video, sheet music (often for piano, sometimes for other instruments) can give you a visual representation of the notes played.\n\n*   **Instrumental Versions (if they exist):** Sometimes, less popular tracks have instrumental or karaoke versions made by fans. These may not be official and can vary in quality.\n\n*   **Covers and Arrangements:** Many musicians create their own covers or arrangements of anime soundtracks. Some might focus on specific instruments or a different arrangement.\n\n**Why a *perfect* multi-track isolation video is unlikely:**\n\n*   **Copyright Issues:** Isolating and sharing the individual tracks from a copyrighted song can be a legal grey area. The owners of the copyright (usually the music publisher and/or record label) may not allow this.\n\n*   **Mixing/Mastering Process:** The final sound of the song is a product of how the individual instruments are mixed and mastered together. Separating them perfectly after that process is difficult and might not sound great on their own.\n\n**How to approach the search:**\n\n1.  **YouTube Search:**\n    *   \"Naruto Strong and Strike isolated instruments\"\n    *   \"Naruto Strong and Strike instrumental\"\n    *   \"Naruto Strong and Strike sheet music\"\n    *   \"Naruto Strong and Strike piano tutorial\"\n\n2.  **Sheet Music Websites:** Look for sheet music on sites like Musicnotes.com, SheetMusicPlus.com, or similar.\n\n3.  **Online Music Forums/Communities:** Try asking in forums dedicated to anime soundtracks, music production, or the Naruto series. Someone might have created a fan-made arrangement or have more specific information.\n\n4.  **Synthesia/Piano Tutorial Websites:** Many websites offer synthesia tutorials for popular songs.\n\n**In short, while finding a definitive video isolating *every* instrument in perfect clarity is unlikely, by combining different resources (the official song, tutorials, sheet music, and fan-made content) you can gain a much better understanding of the individual parts and how they come together to create the iconic sound of \"Strong and Strike.\"**\n",
